      <hedline>
        <hl1>Global Warming: Costly Solutions?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Dan Whittle, Environmental Defense Fund senior attorney, says Nov 11 article on hog farms underscores need for effective controls on factory farm livestock waste</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Nov. 11 news article about hog farm overproduction underscores the need for modern and effective controls on the factory farm livestock waste that is a growing threat to the health of our waterways and skies.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Nov. 11 news article about hog farm overproduction underscores the need for modern and effective controls on the factory farm livestock waste that is a growing threat to the health of our waterways and skies.</p>
        <p>Instead of fostering a real cleanup, Government plans continue the practice of storing and disposing of manure in open-air lagoons and sprayfields that contaminate groundwater and streams, while releasing sickening odors and pollutants into the air. It's time for a temporary moratorium on new or expanding factory farms until real pollution control plans are in place.</p>
        <p>DAN WHITTLE  Senior Attorney  Environmental Defense Fund  Raleigh, N.C., Nov. 11, 1998</p>
      </block>
